    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="175"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/37.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-21">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">January</hi> 21, 1911</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports that in the opinion of the French and German ministers at Port au Prince
                    the Government of the United States should insist upon the maintenance of the
                    status quo and that the pending question should be submitted to arbitration. The
                    British representative was also present at the interview, but declined to
                    concur.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
